title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Generate a Wayang plan that computes, for each nation and each year, the total profit for all parts whose name contains the substring ‘green’. Profit is defined as (l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount)) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity). Join the part, supplier, lineitem, partsupp, orders, and nation tables through their keys. Extract the order year, filter parts so that p_name contains ‘green’, and group the results by nation and year. Output in a textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT p_partkey, p_name FROM part) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val k = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val n = r.getField(1).toString; (k, n) }

operations.table: (SELECT l_orderkey, l_partkey, l_suppkey, l_extendedprice, l_discount, l_quantity FROM lineitem) as X

operations.thatKeyUdf: (t: (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Int)) => t._2

operations.table: (SELECT ps_partkey, ps_suppkey, ps_supplycost FROM partsupp) as X

operations.thisKeyUdf: (t: (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Int)) => t._2
operations.thatKeyUdf: (t: (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Int)) => t._1

operations.table: (SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_orderdate FROM orders) as X
(SELECT c_custkey, c_nationkey FROM customer) as X
(SELECT n_nationkey, n_name FROM nation) as X

operations.thisKeyUdf: (t: (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Int)) => t._2

operations.udf: (t: ((Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Int), (Int, String))) => { val year = t._2._2; val profit = (t._1._3).toDouble * (1.0 - t._1._4) - (t._1._5) * t._1._6; (t._2._1, year, profit) }
(a: (String, String), b: (String, String)) => (a._1, (a._2 as Double) + (b._2 as Double))

log.thoughts: Designed a plan that computes yearly nation-wise total profit for parts with 'green' in their name by joining part, lineitem, partsupp, orders, customer, and nation, then aggregating by nation and year and finally writing results to a text file.
